The beginning of 2020 was quite a ride, it took us a minute to get back into the swing of fun events. But hey, look at us! This Friday, Bingo is back 😝
@synessofactory 💞

Tyler + Kelsea here! We would like to reach out and get emotional for a second.. you guys are cool with that, right??! 😋
✨ Over the last year and a half we have attempted to collaborate with people and businesses that vibe with us and what we are striving to create for our newly found home. We have been able to see our shop and our town with fresh eyes lately, and we are so damn proud! What we see is a community that is appreciating quality time with each other more and more everyday. We see other shops doing artist pop ups, we see more people investing in locally made food, we see a new appreciation for quality over quick. We are so proud of what we have created, and we hope everyone reading this understands YOU had everything to do with it! Without all of our amazing customers, we wouldn’t be able to do any of it. Without our incredible crew, we wouldn’t be able to handle all of the support from all of YOU! ✨ It takes a village to create change, we hope we are the beginning of something great for Monterey and it’s need for new + creative. We love you all so so so so soooo much, thank you for loving us back 💞

Who’s ready for our first of many limited shirts?! Our veteran employee Danielle, who has stuck through every crazy thing that’s happened here at Captain + Stoker is almost a full time designer for us. This is her first solo project and we are so excited about it! Simple and so so us, this long sleeve puppy is the perfect fit. Only comes in black, and we only have 50 (sizes XS-XL). These will be available SATURDAY! 🎉 
Design by @lelecata 
Screen printing by @chrispowers_chrispowers

In the end we are human, mistakes happen + we are trying our best 💞 here are some photos of not so perfect latte art for your viewing pleasure! 😝
